race.description: Barrier Reef Pools C,G&E Maiden Handicap
race.comment: Lots of the chances are back from long breaks. LAKE NAGAMBIE (2) resumes from a long spell after finishing runner-up on debut back in April. Has absolutely bolted in with a trial win so obviously coming along well and can pick up where he left off. MAFIOSA (8) ran on well to place here fresh then wasn't far away when fifth at Warwick latest. Looks close to a win and expected to feature. PAPARACHA (3) is a former Freedman-trained galloper that must have gone amiss before resuming last campaign and is now with a new yard over a year down the track. Fitter for two trials and has shown enough to take this if on song. CHIDGEY (1) is another resuming for a new yard, this time after 18 months after formerly being trained by Ron Quinton. Runner-up in two recent trials and worth watching the betting closely. XTRAVAGANT GIFT (10) was fifth fresh but strips fitter and can give a sight at odds.
